deInterpreterClient Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient |\n| Module | `sdk-python` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Describe the design overview]\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Describe the architecture]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/design.md","time":{"start":1775880378972,"end":1775880378999}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880379001,"sessionID":"ses_28548398affeJ4WszvDmzrUhN8","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab81652001Glk0DUXP4Qon45","messageID":"msg_d7ab7e36b001RscPHZFKHjE2XJ","sessionID":"ses_28548398affeJ4WszvDmzrUhN8","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-efb79a80ef9f48b3aec91f83436ae235","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n2: \n3: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane). The `CodeInterpreterClient` provides lifecycle management (session creation, cleanup), code execution, and file operations.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n18: \n19: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n24: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n25: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n28: \n29: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n30: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n31: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n34: \n35: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n36: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n37: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n42: \n43: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n46: \n47: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n48: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n49: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n52: \n53: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n54: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n55: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n60: \n61: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Create session\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n66: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n67: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Delete session\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n72: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n73: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n78: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n79: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n84: \n85: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Execute command\n88: \n89: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n90: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Files API — write file\n93: \n94: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n95: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Files API — upload file\n98: \n99: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Session header management\n105: \n106: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n111: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n112: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n117: \n118: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Command failure\n121: \n122: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n123: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n124: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n129: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n130: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n135: \n136: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n141: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n142: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Data Structures\n147: \n148: | Class | Fields | Purpose |\n149: |-------|--------|---------|\n150: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `logger`, `cp_client`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client` | Main client for code interpreter sessions |\n151: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url`, `session`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout` | HTTP client for Workload Manager |\n152: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `session_id`, `base_url`, `session`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout` | HTTP client for Router data plane |\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## API Contracts\n157: \n158: ### Control Plane — HTTP\n159: \n160: | Method | Path | Notes |\n161: |--------|------|-------|\n162: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n163: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n164: \n165: ### Data Plane (Code Interpreter) — HTTP\n166: \n167: | Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n168: |--------|---------------|---------------|\n169: | `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n170: | `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n171: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n172: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download |\n173: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ## Dependencies\n178: \n179: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n180: |---------|---------|---------|\n181: | `requests` | — | HTTP client with connection pooling |\n182: | `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT handling |\n183: | `cryptography` | — | Cryptographic operations |\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## File Structure\n188: \n189: | Path | Purpose |\n190: |------|---------|\n191: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports: `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n192: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` class |\n193: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n194: | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports client classes |\n195: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n196: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n197: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` helper |\n198: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` helper |\n199: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` helper |\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ## Validation Checklist\n204: \n205: - [ ] `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` with `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose`, `session_id`\n206: - [ ] Router URL required: raises `ValueError` if missing via arg and env\n207: - [ ] Context manager: `__enter__` returns self, `__exit__` calls `stop()`\n208: - [ ] Session reuse: skips `create_session` when `session_id` provided\n209: - [ ] Data plane init failure cleanup: deletes session, logs warning, re-raises\n210: - [ ] `execute_command`: JSON body `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`, read timeout buffer `+2.0`\n211: - [ ] Non-zero exit: raises `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)`\n212: - [ ] `run_code`: writes timestamped `.py` file, executes via `python3`\n213: - [ ] `write_file`: base64 content, mode `\"0644\"`\n214: - [ ] `upload_file`: multipart POST with `x-agentcube-session-id`\n215: - [ ] `download_file`: GET with `stream=True`\n216: - [ ] `list_files`: GET with query `path`\n217: - [ ] Session header: `x-agentcube-session-id` on all data plane requests\n218: - [ ] Control plane: `POST` `/v1/code-interpreter`, `DELETE` `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`\n219: - [ ] `delete_session`: 404 returns `True`, other failures log and return `False`\n220: - [ ] Auth token: explicit arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n221: - [ ] `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header when token present\n222: - [ ] Default timeouts: read `120s`, connect `5.0s`\n223: - [ ] Exception hierarchy: `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## References\n228: \n229: - `python-sdk/design.md` — AgentCube Python SDK design\n230: - `python-sdk/spec.md` — AgentCube Python SDK specification\n\n(End of file - total 230 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane). The `CodeInterpreterClient` provides lifecycle management (session creation, cleanup), code execution, and file operations.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775880378974,"end":1775880379000}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880379005,"sessionID":"ses_28548398affeJ4WszvDmzrUhN8","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab819fb001kmh7KKETg7Puk7","messageID":"msg_d7ab7e36b001RscPHZFKHjE2XJ","sessionID":"ses_28548398affeJ4WszvDmzrUhN8","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f1f5efca7dfd4c22874865e3da2c72e5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient |\n8: | Module | `sdk-python` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed]\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Exception Hierarchy (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Implement `AgentCubeError` base exception class\n20:   - Purpose: Define base exception for all AgentCube SDK errors\n21:   - File: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n22:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.exceptions import AgentCubeError; raise AgentCubeError('test')\"`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Implement `CommandExecutionError` exception with exit_code, stderr, command\n25:   - Purpose: Exception for non-zero exit code from remote command execution\n26:   - File: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n27:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError; e = CommandExecutionError(1, 'err', 'cmd'); print(e.exit_code)\"`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Implement `SessionError` exception subclass\n30:   - Purpose: Exception for control plane session operations\n31:   - File: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n32:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.exceptions import SessionError; print(isinstance(SessionError(), AgentCubeError))\"`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Implement `DataPlaneError` exception subclass\n35:   - Purpose: Exception for data plane communication errors\n36:   - File: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n37:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.exceptions import DataPlaneError; print(isinstance(DataPlaneError(), AgentCubeError))\"`\n38: \n39: ### Phase 2: Utility Modules (ST-2)\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T2.1**: Implement `create_session()` helper in `utils/http.py`\n42:   - Purpose: Create requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling\n43:   - File: `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n44:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import create_session; s = create_session(); print(type(s))\"`\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `read_token_from_file()` helper in `utils/utils.py`\n47:   - Purpose: Read Kubernetes service account token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n48:   - File: `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n49:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_utils.py::test_read_token_from_file -v`\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `get_logger()` helper in `utils/log.py`\n52:   - Purpose: Return configured logger instance for SDK operations\n53:   - File: `agentcube/utils/log.py`\n54:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.log import get_logger; log = get_logger('test'); print(type(log))\"`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **T2.4**: Create `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` with exports\n57:   - Purpose: Export utility functions from utils package\n58:   - File: `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n59:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils import create_session, read_token_from_file, get_logger; print('OK')\"`\n60: \n61: ### Phase 3: ControlPlaneClient Implementation (ST-3)\n62: \n63: - [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__` with base_url, timeout, connect_timeout\n64:   - Purpose: Initialize HTTP client for Workload Manager API\n65:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n66:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestControlPlaneClientInit -v`\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient` auth token resolution logic\n69:   - Purpose: Resolve auth_token from arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n70:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n71:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestAuthTokenResolution -v`\n72: \n73: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient` Authorization header when token present\n74:   - Purpose: Set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header on session\n75:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n76:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestBearerAuthHeader -v`\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient._resolve_url()` helper\n79:   - Purpose: Resolve workload_manager_url from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var\n80:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n81:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestURLResolution -v`\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.5**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` method\n84:   - Purpose: POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body name, namespace, ttl, metadata\n85:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n86:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestCreateSession -v`\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T3.6**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` return sessionId extraction\n89:   - Purpose: Return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise ValueError if absent\n90:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n91:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestCreateSession::test_create_session_missing_session_id -v`\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T3.7**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` method\n94:   - Purpose: DELETE `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n95:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n96:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestDeleteSession -v`\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T3.8**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` 404 handling\n99:   - Purpose: Return True on 404, log and return False on other failures\n100:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n101:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestDeleteSession::test_delete_session_404_returns_true -v`\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T3.9**: Implement `ControlPlaneClient.close()` method\n104:   - Purpose: Close the HTTP session connection pool\n105:   - File: `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n106:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestClose -v`\n107: \n108: ### Phase 4: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Implementation (ST-4)\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T4.1**: Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__` with session_id, base_url, timeout\n111:   - Purpose: Initialize data plane client with session header setup\n112:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n113:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestDataPlaneClientInit -v`\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.2**: Implement data plane session header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n116:   - Purpose: Set lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` header on all requests\n117:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n118:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestSessionHeader -v`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement data plane `base_url` construction via `urljoin`\n121:   - Purpose: Build base_url from router_url + `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/`\n122:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n123:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestBaseURLConstruction -v`\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `execute_command()` method\n126:   - Purpose: POST `api/execute` with JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`\n127:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n128:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestExecuteCommand -v`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement `execute_command()` read timeout buffer logic\n131:   - Purpose: Set read timeout to `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds to avoid ReadTimeout before PicoD returns exit 124\n132:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n133:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestExecuteCommand::test_execute_command_timeout_buffer -v`\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T4.6**: Implement `execute_command()` non-zero exit handling\n136:   - Purpose: Raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)` when exit_code != 0\n137:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n138:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestExecuteCommand::test_execute_command_nonzero_exit -v`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T4.7**: Implement `write_file()` method\n141:   - Purpose: POST `api/files` with base64 content, path, mode `\"0644\"`\n142:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n143:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestWriteFile -v`\n144: \n145: - [ ] **T4.8**: Implement `upload_file()` method\n146:   - Purpose: POST multipart to `api/files` with `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` and session header\n147:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n148:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestUploadFile -v`\n149: \n150: - [ ] **T4.9**: Implement `download_file()` method\n151:   - Purpose: GET `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True`\n152:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n153:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestDownloadFile -v`\n154: \n155: - [ ] **T4.10**: Implement `list_files()` method\n156:   - Purpose: GET `api/files` with query param `path`\n157:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n158:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestListFiles -v`\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T4.11**: Implement `close()` method for data plane client\n161:   - Purpose: Close the HTTP session\n162:   - File: `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n163:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_data_plane.py::TestClose -v`\n164: \n165: ### Phase 5: CodeInterpreterClient Implementation (ST-5)\n166: \n167: - [ ] **T5.1**: Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` with name, namespace, ttl, workload_manager_url, router_url, auth_token, verbose, session_id\n168:   - Purpose: Initialize main client with all configuration parameters\n169:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n170:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestCodeInterpreterClientInit -v`\n171: \n172: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement Router URL required validation\n173:   - Purpose: Raise ValueError if router_url not provided via arg and ROUTER_URL env var\n174:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n175:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestRouterURLRequired -v`\n176: \n177: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `_resolve_router_url()` helper\n178:   - Purpose: Resolve router_url from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n179:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n180:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestRouterURLResolution -v`\n181: \n182: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement session reuse logic when session_id provided\n183:   - Purpose: Skip create_session call when session_id argument is provided\n184:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n185:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestSessionReuse -v`\n186: \n187: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement session creation via ControlPlaneClient\n188:   - Purpose: Call cp_client.create_session when no session_id provided\n189:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n190:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestSessionCreation -v`\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T5.6**: Implement `_init_data_plane()` private method\n193:   - Purpose: Initialize CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id and router_url\n194:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n195:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestDataPlaneInit -v`\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T5.7**: Implement data plane init failure cleanup\n198:   - Purpose: Log warning, call delete_session(session_id), set session_id to None, re-raise on data plane init failure\n199:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n200:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestDataPlaneInitFailureCleanup -v`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T5.8**: Implement `__enter__()` context manager method\n203:   - Purpose: Return self for context manager usage\n204:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n205:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestContextManager -v`\n206: \n207: - [ ] **T5.9**: Implement `__exit__()` context manager method\n208:   - Purpose: Call stop() on context exit (with or without exception)\n209:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n210:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestContextManager::test_context_manager_calls_stop -v`\n211: \n212: - [ ] **T5.10**: Implement `execute_command()` delegation method\n213:   - Purpose: Delegate to dp_client.execute_command with command and timeout\n214:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n215:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestExecuteCommand -v`\n216: \n217: - [ ] **T5.11**: Implement `run_code()` method for Python execution\n218:   - Purpose: Write timestamped .py file via write_file, execute python3 <file> via execute_command\n219:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n220:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestRunCode -v`\n221: \n222: - [ ] **T5.12**: Implement `run_code()` language detection (python/py/python3)\n223:   - Purpose: Check language is python, py, or python3 before Python execution path\n224:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n225:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestRunCode::test_run_code_python_language -v`\n226: \n227: - [ ] **T5.13**: Implement `write_file()` delegation method\n228:   - Purpose: Delegate to dp_client.write_file\n229:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n230:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestWriteFile -v`\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T5.14**: Implement `upload_file()` delegation method\n233:   - Purpose: Delegate to dp_client.upload_file\n234:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n235:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestUploadFile -v`\n236: \n237: - [ ] **T5.15**: Implement `download_file()` delegation method\n238:   - Purpose: Delegate to dp_client.download_file\n239:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n240:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestDownloadFile -v`\n241: \n242: - [ ] **T5.16**: Implement `list_files()` delegation method\n243:   - Purpose: Delegate to dp_client.list_files\n244:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n245:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestListFiles -v`\n246: \n247: - [ ] **T5.17**: Implement `stop()` method\n248:   - Purpose: Close data-plane session, delete control-plane session if session_id was set, close control plane HTTP session\n249:   - File: `agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n250:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestStop -v`\n251: \n252: ### Phase 6: Package Exports (ST-6)\n253: \n254: - [ ] **T6.1**: Create `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with exports\n255:   - Purpose: Export ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n256:   - File: `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n257:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient; print('OK')\"`\n258: \n259: - [ ] **T6.2**: Update `agentcube/__init__.py` with public exports\n260:   - Purpose: Export CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient from top-level package\n261:   - File: `agentcube/__init__.py`\n262:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient; print('OK')\"`\n263: \n264: - [ ] **T6.3**: Update `agentcube/exceptions.py` exports\n265:   - Purpose: Ensure all exception classes are importable\n266:   - File: `agentcube/exceptions.py`\n267:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.exceptions import AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError; print('OK')\"`\n268: \n269: ### Phase 7: ControlPlaneClient Unit Tests (ST-7)\n270: \n271: - [ ] **T7.1**: Test ControlPlaneClient init with default timeout values\n272:   - Purpose: Verify default read timeout 120s, connect timeout 5.0s\n273:   - File: `tests/test_control_plane.py`\n274:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestControlPlaneClientInit::test_init_default_timeout -v`\n275: \n276: - [ ] **T7.2**: Test ControlPlaneClient init with custom timeout\n277:   - Purpose: Verify custom timeout values are stored\n278:   - File: `tests/test_control_plane.py`\n279:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestControlPlaneClientInit::test_init_custom_timeout -v`\n280: \n281: - [ ] **T7.3**: Test auth token from explicit argument\n282:   - Purpose: Verify token from auth_token arg sets Bearer header\n283:   - File: `tests/test_control_plane.py`\n284:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestAuthTokenResolution::test_auth_token_explicit -v`\n285: \n286: - [ ] **T7.4**: Test auth token from file fallback\n287:   - Purpose: Verify token read from service account file when arg omitted\n288:   - File: `tests/test_control_plane.py`\n289:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestAuthTokenResolution::test_auth_token_from_file -v`\n290: \n291: - [ ] **T7.5**: Test URL resolution from explicit arg\n292:   - Purpose: Verify workload_manager_url from argument\n293:   - File: `tests/test_control_plane.py`\n294:   - Verification: `pytest tests/test_control_plane.py::TestURLResolution::test_url_explicit -v`\n295: \n296: - [ ] **T7.6**: Test URL resolution from env var\n297:   - Purpose: Verify WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var fallback\n29